<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The return value of glob() changed in PHP 5.2.5 when no matches are found (now returns false). See <a href="http://www.php.net/glob">http://www.php.net/glob</a>.</p>

<p>This causes an "Invalid argument supplied for foreach()" on line 281 in release 1.0.3, as well as any other place in Zend_Cache_Backend_File where the return value of glob() is iterated using a foreach loop.</p>

